    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Linwood Seminary</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <date>Feby 9th 1866</date>
            </p>
            <p><addressee>Rev I Leeser</addressee>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir-</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Will you be kind<lb/> enough on the receipt of this to<lb/> send
                    <persName>Wm. H. Simons</persName>
                <hi rend="sup"><placeName>NY</placeName></hi> 50 “Select Sentences,„<lb/> enclosing
                the Bill of them, having<lb/> just heard from my friend <persName>Mrs. M. L.<lb/>
                    Samuel</persName>, of <placeName>Staten Island</placeName>, that <persName>Mrs.
                    S.</persName><lb/> wishes that number sent to her, she<lb/> intending to
                introduce them in her<lb/> school, I trust this will not be<lb/> too much
                trouble.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">All the trouble you have to taken<lb/> for our school has failed, as
                the only<lb/> two <sic>Isrealites</sic>, we had were not bright<lb/> enough to do us
                credit, however<lb/> I still have <hi rend="underline">Trust</hi> &amp; <hi
                    rend="underline">Faith</hi>, that</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><hi rend="underline">Our Father</hi>, will ever provide for<lb/> us that which <hi
                    rend="underline">He</hi> in <hi rend="underline">His</hi> wisdom,<lb/> knows is
                for our good.</p>
            <p>Do you not think it would be a<lb/> good plan to send one of the “Selected
                Sen<lb/>tences” to each of the Jewish Schools, in<lb/>
                <placeName>NY</placeName> as a sample, it might be beneficial<lb/> or to the
                Principals of Sunday Schools,<lb/> in different States, I am anxious<lb/> to
                liquidate my indebtedness to you<lb/> that you must excuse my troubling<lb/> you,
                but as you have ever professed<lb/> yourself &amp; acted as a friend I claim<lb/>
                the indulgence of one,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Ever respectfully</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">Truly yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">H. Emanuel</persName>
            </p>
            <p>To</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <pb n="Envelope"/>
            <p>The</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>1227 Walnut St.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Phila</placeName>
            </p>
